==English==
===Noun===
'''salvation'''
# ''religion'' the process of being saved, the state of having been saved (from hell)

[[it:salvation]]
[[pl:salvation]]
  2.in Christianity salvation is offered by faith alone in Christ alone.  salvation is a mental attitude decision of belief that the payment for sin made on the cross was all that was needed to satisfy God's justice.  salvation is attained by one decision to believe in the Lord Jesus Christ and you will be saved eternally.